item.title: Woot! My first pic with photoshop!
item.dc:creator: @zoss0 Zoss
item.description:
@zoss0 wrote:

[quote=“Mr.Chris, post:17, topic:70881”]Ok, most of you here are talking out of your arses…

Firstly, what is it with brushing being for noobs? It’s a way to make some really nice backgrounds. I encourage you to use them, and get familiar with using them, and Photoshop as a whole. There are some great tutorials at my site, so please use them. They will help you loads.

Also, no, for big style signatures like that, do not stick to one render. I don’t know why kaza otherwise.

Some good ideas for backgrounds are stock images. Have a look at this download. Loads of them. On my site, FastBallz has some great tutorials on stock images.

Good luck![/quote]
OH YEA GO BRUSHES finally, someone stuck up for dem good little things

I love it 8.5/10

item.dc:creator: @Mr.Chris Mr.Chris
item.description:
@Mr.Chris wrote:

Ok, most of you here are talking out of your arses…

Firstly, what is it with brushing being for noobs? It’s a way to make some really nice backgrounds. I encourage you to use them, and get familiar with using them, and Photoshop as a whole. There are some great tutorials at my site, so please use them. They will help you loads.

Also, no, for big style signatures like that, do not stick to one render. I don’t know why kaza otherwise.

Some good ideas for backgrounds are stock images. Have a look at this download. Loads of them. On my site, FastBallz has some great tutorials on stock images.

Good luck!
